{
  "text": "where \u03c8 j and \u03c7 j are the Fermi partners of the \u03d5 \u00b1 j scalars. (\u03d5 \u00b1 j , \u03c8 j , \u03c7 j ) constitute altogether the 4d N = 2 free hypermultiplets. Using the splitting principle by factorizing \u01eb + as \u01eb\u03b7 + and \u01eb + = \u01eb\u03b7 + , and using eqs (4.10-11), we get [CITATION_1] or equivalenty",
